Check for good soil drainage. You want soil to drain water at the rate of about a foot an hour to prevent root rot. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/93/Create-a-Perennial-Garden-Step-1Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Create-a-Perennial-Garden-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/93/Create-a-Perennial-Garden-Step-1Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Create-a-Perennial-Garden-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Choose a location that has plenty of air circulation. This limits diseases in perennial plants. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/a1/Create-a-Perennial-Garden-Step-1Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Create-a-Perennial-Garden-Step-1Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/a1/Create-a-Perennial-Garden-Step-1Bullet3.jpg/v4-760px-Create-a-Perennial-Garden-Step-1Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
